-- Hong Kong Air Pollution Reaches `Very High' 109 Level in Central District
-- B y   D i r k   B e v e r i d g e
-- 2010-10-25T01:06:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/hong-kong-air-pollution-reaches-very-high-109-level-in-central-district.html
Hong Kong’s Air Pollution Index
reached a “very high” level of 109 in Central business
district as of 8 a.m. today, the city’s Environmental Protection
Department said on its website. Readings above 100 at roadside
monitoring stations trigger a government warning that people
with heart or respiratory ailments should avoid prolonged stays
in heavy traffic areas.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dirk Beveridge at 
 dbeveridge1@bloomberg.net  